  "metadata": {
    "title": "NHS Waiting Times Explorer",
    "lastUpdated": "2026-05-16",
    "source": "NHS England RTT Statistics, BMA, King's Fund",
    "period": "March 2026 (latest available)",
    "lastReleaseNotes": "NHS England RTT March 2026 (published 14 May 2026): waiting list fell to 7.11m treatments (~6.02m individual patients), lowest in 3.5 years and down 515k since July 2024; YoY reduction of 312k — largest in 16 years. 65.3% within 18 weeks (interim 65% target met — first time hit since 2015), but still well below long-term 92% standard. Median wait 11.3 weeks; 92nd percentile 38.3 weeks. NHS England framed this as a 'huge moment'; Health Service Journal noted 'majority of improvement' in March driven by a 'record' spike in 'unreported removals' (data-validation caveat). Cancer 28-day faster diagnosis 79.4% (vs 75% target — met); 31-day from decision to treat 92.8% (vs 96%); 62-day urgent 72.8% (vs 85%). Regional and specialty breakdowns below carry the February 2026 distribution pending extraction of the March SPN PDF."
  },
